Usage:

First time usage require: devpkg -S to initialize database system
    This is only required only one time.

In order to install any package:
do  devpkg -F <url containing the package to be installed>, this
    will download the package into your /tmp/ directory

next do devpkg -I or devpkg -I -m <m opts> -c <c opts> -i <i opts>

If you want to build the pkg but not install it
   devpkg -B or devpkg -B -m <> -c <> -i <>

To list packages already installed: devpkg -L
